			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Silicon carbide is an exceedingly hard, synthetically produced crystalline compound of silicon and carbon. It has been an important material for sandpapers, grinding wheels, and cutting tools since the late 19th century. It is a wide bandgap semiconductor that is currently contributing to a deep transformation of power electronics, because of its outstanding combination of physical and electronic properties. It is used as an abrasive and as a refractory and in electric resistors.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">碳化硅是一种非常坚硬的硅和碳的合成结晶化合物。自 19 世纪末以来，它一直是砂纸、砂轮和切割工具的重要材料。它是一种宽带隙半导体，由于其出色的物理和电子特性组合，目前正在推动电力电子技术的深入变革。它可用作磨料、耐火材料和电阻器。</common:generalComment>
